        },
        "content": "## Recommended Alert Rules\n\nBased on the thresholds used in this dashboard, consider implementing these Prometheus alert rules:\n\n### Critical Alerts\n- **ServiceDown**: `up == 0` - Service is not responding\n- **HighCPUUsage**: `100 - (avg(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode=\"idle\"}[5m])) * 100) > 80` - Node CPU > 80%\n- **HighMemoryUsage**: `(node_memory_MemTotal_bytes - node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes) / node_memory_MemTotal_bytes * 100 > 85` - Node memory > 85%\n- **HighDiskUsage**: `100 - ((node_filesystem_avail_bytes{mountpoint=\"/\"} * 100) / node_filesystem_size_bytes{mountpoint=\"/\"}) > 90` - Disk usage > 90%\n\n### Warning Alerts\n- **HighTemperature**: `node_hwmon_temp_celsius > 70` - Temperature above 70°C\n- **HighSystemLoad**: `node_load5 > 4` - System load above number of CPU cores\n- **NetworkErrors**: `rate(node_network_receive_errs_total[5m]) > 1` - Network errors detected\n- **SecurityAlerts**: Failed authentication attempts above baseline\n\n### Configuration\nTo implement these alerts:\n1. Add alert rules to Prometheus configuration\n2. Configure Alertmanager for notifications\n3. Set up notification channels (email, Slack, etc.)\n4. Test alert firing and recovery\n\n### Monitoring Best Practices\n- Set appropriate alert thresholds based on your environment\n- Implement alert fatigue prevention (grouping, inhibition)\n- Ensure alerts are actionable and include runbook links\n- Monitor alert manager itself for reliability",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
